CAPE TOWN – Twenty-five students from the University of the Western Cape will spend the next seven days behind bars. They appeared at the Bellville Magistrate’s Court on Friday on charges of public violence. The group was arrested on Wednesday after violent clashes on campus, during which a building was set alight. UPDATE: UWC suspends face-to-face lectures; res is set alight The state requested a seven-day postponement to gather bail information. Some of the students will be sent to the Goodwood Correctional Facility and some to Pollsmoor Prison. They are due to return to court next Friday, but their lawyer, Syndey Tsotso, said he would be applying to get the students released from prison sooner. eNCA